    <item>
      <title>Better dmesg in five minutes</title>
      <link>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2024/11/17/better-dmesg/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 17 Nov 2024 15:52:00 -0500</pubDate>
      <guid>https://purpleidea.com/blog/2024/11/17/better-dmesg/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I last wrote about &lt;code&gt;dmesg&lt;/code&gt; in &lt;a href=&#34;https://purpleidea.com/blog/2016/08/29/live-dmesg-following/&#34;&gt;2016&lt;/a&gt;. It&#xA;has mostly not changed since then, but I&amp;rsquo;ve changed my setup slightly. Here&amp;rsquo;s a&#xA;short article about what I did so that you can do it too, and so that I can&#xA;remember for the next time.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;text-decoration:underline; font-weight: bold;&#34;&gt;Previously&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Previous I had a bash alias which looked like this:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#f8f8f8;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;alias dmesg=&amp;#39;dmesg --follow || dmesg&amp;#39;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;since some machines didn&amp;rsquo;t yet support the &lt;code&gt;--follow&lt;/code&gt; flag.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
